      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_7fb30c141ba6b3d5c5bea9d172f0a1e6">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Burmese Archive Collection (MS 113). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d97df5af6fa3cc01104a08a54c11c9a4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>A collection of photocopies of approximately forty items dealing with Independent Burma, 1943-1945. The documents record the establishment of Independent Burma in August 1943 and continue with letters, memoranda and other papers dealing with the problems of continued Japanese occupation. The major figure is Dr. Ba Maw who was head of state in the Burmese government.</p>
         <p>The papers are arranged in chronological order. Items in both Japanese and Burmese are included, most of which are accompanied by English translations.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
